## The Scarce Act of Live Electronic Music: Rheome’s Role

Even as music production, curation, and live performance proliferate, scarcity persists—but in a very specific place. Skilled producers release music daily; playlists, curators, and DJs compete for attention; clubs, festivals, and livestreams abound. Yet much of what is considered “live” electronic music today is still pre-composed, stem-based, or DJ sets playing recorded tracks. The act of truly improvisational, real-time electronic creation—where every note, texture, and effect is decided in the moment—is rare.

